    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-02-21T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-02-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="403"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <head>403. Telegram From the Ambassador in Chile (<persName corresp="#p_LCB1"
                        type="from">Lyon</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                        State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d403fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 725.11/2–2157. Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-02-21T11:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1957—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>436. Reference proposal invite President Ibanez visit US. Embassy considers
                    important and timely Ibanez now be invited. He has been surprisingly and
                    gratifyingly unwavering in anti-inflationary fight, and invitation would
                    constitute our endorsement and support Chile’s action this program which can
                    serve as example Latin America and rest world. Invitation should also assure
                    continuance program after elections and would give lift to Chile’s morale which
                    needed this juncture due to decline copper price, difficult nitrate situation
                    and general political picture. It would also constitute valuable psychological
                    counter frequent charges here and other American Republics that US more
                    sympathetic hemisphere dictatorships than to democracies.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d403fn2">In telegram 428 to <persName corresp="#p_RSI1"
                            >Santiago</persName>, March 7, the Department informed <persName
                            corresp="#p_LCB1">Lyon</persName> that an invitation to <persName
                            corresp="#p_ICGC1">Ibáñez</persName> was under consideration, but that a
                        decision was not expected before the middle of March. (<hi rend="italic"
                            >Ibid.</hi>)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LCB1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Lyon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
